==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Producers goods
<hw>Pro*duc"er's goods</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(Polit. Econ.)</fld>
<def>Goods that satisfy wants only indirectly as factors in the
production of other goods, such as tools and raw material; -- called
also <altname>instrumental goods</altname>, <altname>auxiliary
goods</altname>, <altname>intermediate goods</altname>, or
<altname>goods of the second and higher orders</altname>, and disting.
from <contr>consumers' goods</contr>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Producer's rent</ent>⟦br⟧
<ent>Producer's surplus</ent>⟦br⟧
